- **LHS**: `Prod.fst <$> ((simulateQ loggingOracle).toFun (pSpec.FullTranscript × StmtOut × WitOut) (@Prover.run ι oSpec StmtIn StmtOut WitIn WitOut n pSpec stmt wit prover)).run`
  - `@Prover.run ...` is a term of type `OracleComp (oSpec + (challengeOracleInterface pSpec).spec) (pSpec.FullTranscript × StmtOut × WitOut)`.
  - `((simulateQ loggingOracle).toFun ...).run` is applying `simQ` to this term. The `toFun` part is converting the `OracleComp` term to a function type. So `simQ` is being applied to this function.
